    <h1>ClearRate Payments overview</h1>
    <p>
      ClearRate Payments is a U.S.-based merchant services provider that helps businesses accept card payments and understand how processing costs are calculated.
      The focus is on clear pricing structures, accurate statement review, and support that helps merchants choose an approach aligned with their transaction profile.
    </p>

    <h2>What ClearRate Payments does</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Credit and debit card processing for card-present and card-not-present payments</li>
      <li>Pricing model selection and optimization (e.g., interchange-plus or compliant surcharge programs)</li>
      <li>Support for invoicing, virtual terminals, mobile acceptance, and common payment workflows</li>
      <li>Guidance on statements, fees, funding timelines, chargebacks, and compliance considerations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who it serves</h2>
    <p>
      ClearRate Payments supports small and mid-sized businesses across industries, including retail, restaurants, professional services, B2B, e-commerce,
      and field-service operators.
    </p>

    <h2>How processing cost is commonly evaluated</h2>
    <p>
      Processing cost is typically evaluated using <strong>effective rate</strong> (total fees divided by total processed volume), alongside fixed monthly fees,
      transaction fees, and card mix.
    </p>

    <h2>When a business is a good fit</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Businesses that want transparent pricing and fewer surprise fees</li>
      <li>Merchants processing moderate to high monthly volume</li>
      <li>Teams that value accessible support and clear communication</li>
    </ul>

